<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9165b02-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8715"><num value="8715">§ 8715.</num><heading> Jurisdiction of courts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The district courts of the United States have original jurisdiction, concurrent with the United States Court of Federal Claims, of a civil action or claim against the United States founded on this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb9165b03-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/554">Pub. L. 89–554</ref>, <date date="1966-09-06">Sept. 6, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/599">80 Stat. 599</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/97/164/tI/s160/a/2">Pub. L. 97–164, title I, § 160(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="1982-04-02">Apr. 2, 1982</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/48">96 Stat. 48</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/572/tIX/s902/b/1">Pub. L. 102–572, title IX, § 902(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1992-10-29">Oct. 29, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/4516">106 Stat. 4516</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
